    {
      "id": "https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/05/260506225428.htm",
      "url": "https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/05/260506225428.htm",
      "title": "[ScienceDaily] New “Trojan horse” obesity drug supercharges weight loss in early tests",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=www.sciencedaily.com&amp;sz=128\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\nResearchers have created a next-generation obesity drug that works like a “Trojan horse,” using GLP-1/GIP signals to slip a powerful metabolic enhancer directly into target cells. In mice, it outperformed existing treatments—curbing appetite, increasing weight loss, and improving blood sugar levels. Because the extra drug acts only where it’s needed, it can be used at much lower doses, potentially reducing side effects.",
      "date_published": "2026-05-07T10:37:46+00:00",
      "authors": [
        {
          "name": "ScienceDaily",
          "url": "https://www.sciencedaily.com"
        }
      ],
      "image": "https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=www.sciencedaily.com&sz=128"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/05/260506225233.htm",
      "url": "https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/05/260506225233.htm",
      "title": "[ScienceDaily] Scientists discover why Ozempic works better for some people",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=www.sciencedaily.com&amp;sz=128\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\nSome people taking Ozempic-like diabetes drugs may be getting dramatically better results for a surprising reason: why they overeat in the first place. A year-long study in Japan found that people who tend to eat because tempting food looks or smells irresistible were much more likely to lose weight and improve blood sugar levels on GLP-1 medications. But people who eat mainly in response to stress, sadness, or emotional struggles didn’t see the same long-term benefits.",
      "date_published": "2026-05-07T10:11:48+00:00",
      "authors": [
